<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="196" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,429]" pageId="8" pageNumber="196">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,331,356]" pageId="8" pageNumber="196">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Large flat bucklers cover on ventral surface of disc and caudal peduncle; teeth on vomer forming a very wide band; subopercular buckler elongate, slightly curved, bears two forward-directed spines at tip; pectoralfin rays 
<number box="[243,312,404,428]" pageId="8" pageNumber="196" value="14.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="14.0">14–15</number>
(mainly 
<number box="[414,445,404,428]" pageId="8" pageNumber="196" value="15.0">15</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
